title: New baby orca spotted with mother
text:
New baby orca spotted with mother By Associated Press | September 8, 2015 @ 8:48 am Share 
SEATTLE (AP) -- The Puget Sound orca pod has a new member, which brings to five the number of new baby orcas born to the region's three pods since December. 
The new calf, named L122, was spotted Monday by members of the Center for Whale Research. The baby orca was swimming with her mother L91, a 20-year-old orca. 
The researchers were in the area conducting aerial measurements of the whales when they spotted the pair near Sooke, British Columbia. 
The mother and calf spent most of Monday "fishing" in Haro Strait, just west of San Juan Island, and were later joined by J and K pod members. 
Researchers say they hope this year's 'baby boom' represents a turn-around in what has been a negative population trend in recent years.
